  "en_notes_asad": [
    {
      "note_no": "108",
      "note": "According to most of the classical commentators, the particle li prefixed to the verb yudillu (\"they are leading astray\") represents in this context the so-called lam al-'aqibah (\"the [letter] lam denoting a consequence\") and does not, as in many other instances, express a purpose or an intent (\"in order that\" or \"to the end that\"). My rendering of this li as \"with the result that\" is meant to bring out Moses' moral indignation at the perversity of Pharaoh and his great ones who, instead of being grateful to God for His bounty, are using their power to corrupt their own people."
    }
